channel.title: Eclipse Help
channel.description:
Hey guys.
I have been using Eclipse with Project Exile source for about 4 hours now, just messing around exploring options and files and I've had trouble exploring the SRC under the project explorer, so I've resorted to File>Open File>(Searching in the server files for a line or number or code)>Opening that File in Eclipse. Doesn't seem very efficient but it's getting the job done for now.
My question is this; Eclise is throwing over 800 errors when I build(compile). These errors were present before I changed anything, as i've only changed a few dialogue lines and item prices. How will this affect my server?
See my other thread [url=https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,662404]here[/url].

item.title: Eclipse Help
item.dc:creator: @Murk3d09 Murk3d09
item.description:
@Murk3d09 wrote:

Ashi:

If you’re getting errors while compiling, anything that you change will not be in effect. That’s how it’ll effect your server.

Lol yea, thanks. xD I just realized that I put errors instead of warnings… Not nearly as threatening to the server i’m assuming.
